  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Purchaser",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & Requirements</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee and manage all purchasing activities for company projects, especially related to <strong>tunnel works / construction materials</strong>.</li><li>Source, negotiate, and purchase materials, equipment, and services from local and overseas suppliers.</li><li>Handle procurement from <strong>Taobao </strong>and other Chinese platforms – including communication, order tracking, and shipment coordination.</li><li>Evaluate supplier quotations to ensure compliance with technical and commercial specifications.</li><li>Maintain and update supplier information, purchase orders, and inventory records.</li><li>Coordinate with project and site teams to ensure timely delivery of materials.</li><li>Monitor market trends and identify cost-saving opportunities.</li><li>Prepare purchasing reports and support management in procurement planning.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Minimum 2–3 years of purchasing experience</strong>, must have <strong>tunnel construction experience</strong></li><li><strong>Able to communicate fluently in Mandarin and English</strong> (both spoken and written) – essential for dealing with Chinese suppliers.</li><li><strong>Hands-on experience with online procurement platforms</strong> such as Taobao, Alibaba, and other</li><li><strong>Able to work long hours</strong> and handle urgent orders under pressure.</li><li><strong>Independent, responsible, and detail-oriented</strong> with strong negotiation skills.</li><li><strong>Proficient in Microsoft Office and online research tools.</strong></li><li><strong>Energetic, fast learner, and results-driven.</strong></li><li><strong>Able to start immediately</strong></li></ul>",
